{"title":"AdventureWorks","markdown":{"headingText":"AdventureWorks","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\nWe use the AdventureWorks sample database from Microsoft as our primary dataset.\n\nThe AdventureWorks database is a realistic, relational dataset that models a mid-sized manufacturing and sales company called *Adventure Works Cycles*.  \n\nIt contains data about products, sales, customers, employees, vendors, and production processes, making it ideal for demonstrating complete, data-driven application pipelines.\n\nIn this course, the dataset acts as the shared backend for a collection of interactive AI-powered applications. All apps connect to a Microsoft SQL Server instance that hosts the AdventureWorks data.\n\n\n## What We’ll Build with AdventureWorks\n\nWe use the dataset to explore the full AI + data workflow — from SQL querying to intelligent front-end delivery.\n\nExample applications include:\n\n| Area | Technology | Description |\n|------|-------------|--------------|\n| Natural-language data exploration | Gradio | Ask questions like *“What were the top 5 products by revenue in 2023?”* and get Gemini-generated SQL, data, and charts. |\n| Interactive forecasting | Gradio / Streamlit | Build time-series forecasts (e.g., monthly sales by region or product line) with adjustable parameters and downloadable summaries. |\n| Automated reporting | Gradio + Quarto | Generate AI-enhanced PDF reports directly from AdventureWorks data, complete with charts and narrative insights. |\n| Web dashboards | Next.js | Create modern dashboards that connect to the same SQL backend and use Gemini for intelligent query suggestions. |\n\n\n\n\n## Architecture\n\n```{mermaid}\nflowchart LR\n  A[Gemini API] -->|SQL generation + insights| B[Gradio / Streamlit / Next.js Apps]\n  B -->|Queries| C[(AdventureWorks SQL Server)]\n  C -->|Results + Metadata| B\n  B -->|Visuals + Reports| D[Users]\n```\n\nAdventureWorks SQL Server is the single source of truth.\n\nGemini translates natural language into SQL and generates insights.\n\nThe front ends (Gradio, Streamlit, Next.js) deliver data, forecasts, and reports interactively.\n\n\n## Access and API Keys\n\nAll participants will receive API keys and connection credentials to access the shared AdventureWorks database.\n\nThese keys provide secure, authenticated access from the different front-end applications.\n\n::: {.callout-important}\nThe API keys and database connection strings will be distributed by the course instructor.\nEach key is personal and must not be shared publicly or stored in version control.\n:::\n\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":"auto","echo":false,"output":true,"warning":false,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"ipynb-shell-interactivity":null,"plotly-connected":true,"engine":"markdown"},"render":{"keep-tex":false,"keep-typ":false,"keep-source":false,"keep-hidden":false,"prefer-html":false,"output-divs":true,"output-ext":"html","fig-align":"default","fig-pos":null,"fig-env":null,"code-fold":"none","code-overflow":"wrap","code-link":false,"code-line-numbers":false,"code-tools":false,"tbl-colwidths":"auto","merge-includes":true,"inline-includes":false,"preserve-yaml":false,"latex-auto-mk":true,"latex-auto-install":true,"latex-clean":true,"latex-min-runs":1,"latex-max-runs":10,"latex-makeindex":"makeindex","latex-makeindex-opts":[],"latex-tlmgr-opts":[],"latex-input-paths":[],"latex-output-dir":null,"link-external-icon":false,"link-external-newwindow":false,"self-contained-math":false,"format-resources":[],"notebook-links":true},"pandoc":{"standalone":true,"wrap":"none","default-image-extension":"png","to":"html","number-sections":true,